// Diagram Utilities
// Functions for inspecting and manipulating Mermaid diagram source: direction detection,
// node/edge location, node ID generation, and node definition building.

NODE_TYPES constant maps names ('terminal', 'state', 'decision', 'action') to their
Mermaid bracket syntax and fill/stroke style strings.

FUNCTION detectDirection(content) -> DiagramDirection | null            EXPORT
  Match the first line containing 'graph' or 'flowchart' followed by a direction keyword (LR, TD, RL, BT).
  Return the direction, or null if not found.

---

FUNCTION toggleDirection(content) -> ToggleDirectionResult              EXPORT
  CALLS: detectDirection (diagramUtils)
  Detect the current direction. Toggle it: LR<->TD, RL<->BT, no direction -> TD.
  Replace the direction keyword in the content, preserving original case.
  IF no direction exists, insert the new one after the diagram type keyword.
  Return { content, oldDirection, newDirection }.

---

FUNCTION escapeRegex(str) -> string [private]
  Escape all regex special characters in a string.

---

FUNCTION extractNodeId(element) -> string | null                        EXPORT
  Walk up the DOM from the given element.
  Check for data-id attribute (newer Mermaid format).
  ELSE check for id attribute matching the pattern flowchart-NodeId-<number> (older format).
  Return the node ID, or null if not found.

---

FUNCTION extractEdgeInfo(element) -> { source, target, label? } | null EXPORT
  Walk up the DOM to find an element with class 'edgePath'.
  Parse the edge ID to extract source and target node names.
  Return null if no edge container is found.

---

FUNCTION findNodeLine(nodeId, content) -> number | null                 EXPORT
  Split content into lines. Search for a line where nodeId is followed by a shape bracket.
  Return the 1-indexed line number, or null if not found.

---

FUNCTION findEdgeLine(source, target, content) -> number | null         EXPORT
  Search for a line matching the pattern: source --> target (or similar arrow syntax).
  Return the 1-indexed line number, or null if not found.

---

FUNCTION generateNodeId(content, prefix) -> string                      EXPORT
  Extract all existing node IDs from the content.
  Find the lowest integer suffix for the given prefix that doesn't already exist.
  Return the unique ID.

---

FUNCTION buildNodeDefinition(id, label, type) -> string                 EXPORT
  Return the Mermaid node definition string: id<open>"label"<close> using the shape brackets for the given type.

---

FUNCTION buildNodeStyle(id, type) -> string                             EXPORT
  Return a Mermaid style statement: style id <fill/stroke CSS> using the style string for the given type.
